hm2AgentDot1xPortConfigTable.description: A table for dot1x enhanced Port details and associated functionality.

hm2AgentDot1xPortConfigEntry.name: hm2AgentDot1xPortConfigEntry

hm2AgentDot1xPortControlMode.name: hm2AgentDot1xPortControlMode
hm2AgentDot1xPortControlMode.description: Dot1x port control mode of this port.The Port control mode . The port control mode for this interface can take the following values , force-unauthorized - the port is in unauthorized mode, auto-Port based mode. If a client authenticates suscessfully, then the interface is authorized . Otherwise, the port is in unauthorized mode. If more than one clients are attached to the port , then only one client needs to authenticate to allow other clients access. force-authorized - The port is placed in authorized mode multiClient - If more than one client is attached to the port, then each client needs to authenticate separately. This object depcreates dot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl object in IEEE8021-PAE-MIB

hm2AgentDot1xGuestVlanId.name: hm2AgentDot1xGuestVlanId
hm2AgentDot1xGuestVlanId.description: Specifies the Guest Vlan of the port. A port will be moved to its Guest Vlan if no client sucessfully authenticates on that port for the Guest Vlan Period. A value of zero indicates no Guest Vlan is configured for the interface.

hm2AgentDot1xGuestVlanPeriod.name: hm2AgentDot1xGuestVlanPeriod
hm2AgentDot1xGuestVlanPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the guestVlanPeriod constant currently in use for Guest Vlan Assignment for the port .

hm2AgentDot1xUnauthenticatedVlan.name: hm2AgentDot1xUnauthenticatedVlan
hm2AgentDot1xUnauthenticatedVlan.description: Specifies the Unauthenticated Vlan of the port. A port will be moved to its unauthenticated Vlan if the client authenticates unsucessfully on that port . A value of zero indicates no Unauthenticated Vlan is configured for the port.

hm2AgentDot1xMaxUsers.name: hm2AgentDot1xMaxUsers
hm2AgentDot1xMaxUsers.description: Specifies the maximum users or clients that can authenticate on this port when the port control mode is multiClient.

hm2AgentDot1xPortVlanAssigned.name: hm2AgentDot1xPortVlanAssigned
hm2AgentDot1xPortVlanAssigned.description: Specifies the vlan the port is assigned to by Dot1x . Only relevant if the port control mode of the port is auto.

hm2AgentDot1xPortVlanAssignedReason.name: hm2AgentDot1xPortVlanAssignedReason
hm2AgentDot1xPortVlanAssignedReason.description: Reason the port is assigned to the vlan specified by hm2AgentDot1xPortVlanAssigned . Only relevant if the port control mode of the port is auto.

hm2AgentDot1xPortSessionTimeout.name: hm2AgentDot1xPortSessionTimeout
hm2AgentDot1xPortSessionTimeout.description: Specifies the session timeout value assigned by the Radius server for this port . Only relevant if the port control mode of the port is auto.

hm2AgentDot1xPortTerminationAction.name: hm2AgentDot1xPortTerminationAction
hm2AgentDot1xPortTerminationAction.description: Specifies the session termination action assigned by the Radius Server .This is the action taken when the session times out . Only relevant if the port control mode of the port is auto.

hm2AgentDot1xPortMABenabled.name: hm2AgentDot1xPortMABenabled
hm2AgentDot1xPortMABenabled.description: Specifies if Mac-based bypass authentication is configured for the port.

hm2AgentDot1xPortMABenabledOperational.name: hm2AgentDot1xPortMABenabledOperational
hm2AgentDot1xPortMABenabledOperational.description: Displays the operational value of the Mac-based authentication bypass mode (MAB) on the port.

hm2AgentDot1xClientConfigTable.name: hm2AgentDot1xClientConfigTable
hm2AgentDot1xClientConfigTable.description: A table for dot1x Client details and associated functionality.

hm2AgentDot1xClientConfigEntry.name: hm2AgentDot1xClientConfigEntry
hm2AgentDot1xClientConfigEntry.description: Represents entry for port config table.

hm2AgentDot1xClientMacAddress.name: hm2AgentDot1xClientMacAddress
hm2AgentDot1xClientMacAddress.description: Specifies the client MAC address of the client.

hm2AgentDot1xLogicalPort.name: hm2AgentDot1xLogicalPort
hm2AgentDot1xLogicalPort.description: Specifies the client MAC address of the client .

hm2AgentDot1xInterface.name: hm2AgentDot1xInterface
hm2AgentDot1xInterface.description: Specifies the physical interface to which the client is attached .

hm2AgentDot1xClientAuthPAEstate.name: hm2AgentDot1xClientAuthPAEstate
hm2AgentDot1xClientAuthPAEstate.description: The current value of the Authenticator PAE state machine for the client.

hm2AgentDot1xClientBackendState.name: hm2AgentDot1xClientBackendState
hm2AgentDot1xClientBackendState.description: The current state of the Backend Authentication state machine.

hm2AgentDot1xClientUserName.name: hm2AgentDot1xClientUserName
hm2AgentDot1xClientUserName.description: Specifies the username with which the client is authenticated to the Radius server . This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

hm2AgentDot1xClientSessionTime.name: hm2AgentDot1xClientSessionTime
hm2AgentDot1xClientSessionTime.description: Specifies the time elapsed in seconds since the client was authenticated in this session. This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

hm2AgentDot1xClientFilterID.name: hm2AgentDot1xClientFilterID
hm2AgentDot1xClientFilterID.description: Specifies the Filter ID or Diffserv Policy name to be applied to the session . This vlaue is populated only if it has been assigned by the RADIUS server. This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

hm2AgentDot1xClientVlanAssigned.name: hm2AgentDot1xClientVlanAssigned
hm2AgentDot1xClientVlanAssigned.description: Specifies the vlan the client is associated with by Dot1x . This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

hm2AgentDot1xClientVlanAssignedReason.name: hm2AgentDot1xClientVlanAssignedReason
hm2AgentDot1xClientVlanAssignedReason.description: Reason the client is associated to the vlan specified by hm2AgentDot1xClientVlanAssigned . This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

hm2AgentDot1xClientSessionTimeout.name: hm2AgentDot1xClientSessionTimeout
hm2AgentDot1xClientSessionTimeout.description: Specifies the session time remaining for the client if assigned by the Radius server . A value of 0 indicates that no session timeout was assigned by the RADIUS server. This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

hm2AgentDot1xClientTerminationAction.name: hm2AgentDot1xClientTerminationAction
hm2AgentDot1xClientTerminationAction.description: Specifies the session termination action assigned by the Radius Server . This is the action taken when the session times out . This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

hm2AgentDot1xMonitorModeEnabled.name: hm2AgentDot1xMonitorModeEnabled
hm2AgentDot1xMonitorModeEnabled.description: Enable/Disable Dot1x Monitor mode Support on the switch.

hm2AgentDot1xMonitorModeClients.name: hm2AgentDot1xMonitorModeClients
hm2AgentDot1xMonitorModeClients.description: Retrieves the number of clients that got authenticated by Monitor mode globally.

hm2AgentDot1xNonMonitorModeClients.name: hm2AgentDot1xNonMonitorModeClients
hm2AgentDot1xNonMonitorModeClients.description: Retrieves the number of clients that are granted access by Dot1x with no monitor mode enabled.

hm2AgentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultTable.description: A table to display the dot1x monitor mode results.

hm2AgentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultEntry.name: hm2AgentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultEntry
hm2AgentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultEntry.description: Represents Dot1x Authentication results for a Dot1x Authentication History table.

hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIfaceIndex.name: hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIfaceIndex
hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIfaceIndex.description: This object represents the physical Bridge Port on which dot1x Auth event might be received.

hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIndex.name: hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIndex
hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIndex.description: Reference to the Dot1x Authentication history table maintained.

hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultTimeStamp.name: hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultTimeStamp
hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultTimeStamp.description: Specifies the exact time of Dot1x Authentication event information occurred maintained in the history table.

hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAge.name: hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAge
hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAge.description: Time since the authentication entry was added to the history table. It is displayed in days, hours, minutes, and seconds.

hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultMacAddress.name: hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultMacAddress
hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultMacAddress.description: Specifies the client.s MAC Address maintained in the Dot1x Authentication history table.

hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanId.name: hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanId
hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanId.description: Specifies the VLANID maintained in the history table (It is the VLANID on which the Dot1x table. It is the VLANID which is failed to associate to the port during authentication process. The VLANID is identified distinctly by the Reason code for the respective entry. Valid only when the reason code is set to 13 (VLAN assignment failure). In all the other cases, VLANID is set to 0.

hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAuthStatus.name: hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAuthStatus
hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAuthStatus.description: Specifies the Dot1x Authentication status (Success or Failure) for the Dot1x Authentication event takes place.

hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAccessStat.name: hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAccessStatus
hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAccessStat.description: Authentication access status indicates the exact status of the dot1x client. Granted means the client is allowed access to the network using dot1x or monitor mode. Denied means the client is not allowed access to the network.

hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultFilterID.name: hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultFilterID
hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultFilterID.description: Specifies the Filter ID or Diffserv Policy name assigned by the RADIUS server. This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanAssign.name: hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanAssigned
hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanAssign.description: Specifies the VLANID maintained in the history table (It is the VLANID Assigned to a Port or Client authenticate).

hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanAssign.name: hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanAssignedType
hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanAssign.description: Specifies the VLAN Assigned Reason maintained in the history table.

hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultReasonCode.name: hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultReasonCode
hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultReasonCode.description: Specifies the Dot1x authentication reason refered by the result index on a port.

hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultsClear.name: hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultsClear
hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultsClear.description: When set to enable(1), all Dot1x Authentication History information will be reset.

hm2AgentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultClearT.name: hm2AgentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultClearTable
hm2AgentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultClearT.description: A table to clear the dot1x monitor mode results per interface.

hm2AgentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultClearE.description: Represents to clear the Dot1x Authentication results for a Dot1x Authentication History table.

hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIfIndex.name: hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIfIndex
hm2AgentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIfIndex.description: This object represents the physical Bridge Port on which dot1x Auth event might be received.

hm2AgentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultsClear.name: hm2AgentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultsClear
hm2AgentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultsClear.description: When set to enable(1), all Dot1x Authentication History information for the given port will be reset. The value is write-only. Attempt to read will return disable(2).
